<!--
Perceive-act loop, v2. The same shared always-socket agent (`agent.bsx`) and the same
in-process mock head as v1, but the mock body is swapped for a real wgpu body: a 3d fox
that drives off the model's `apply-heading`. That one client swap is the only change from
v1. Run it with the windowed render stack plus the sockets backend:

    cargo run -p beet-cli --features winit,sockets -- --main=examples/perceive_act/main-v2.bsx --root=. --server=socket

`<WgpuBody>` opens a window with the fox over a ground plane and serves `apply-heading` by
mapping the chosen `Heading` onto the fox's `DifferentialDrive` through the agnostic
`SetDrive` leaf (drive a step, then stop), the same command that will drive the v3 robot.
The head still captures the floor-photo fixtures, speaks via `tts` and logs the emotion.

Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY` (the agent) and the kokoro `tts` on PATH for spoken audio.
-->
<Fragment>
	<Template src="examples/perceive_act/agent.bsx"/>
	<!-- in-process clients, each its own socket root -->
	<MockHead url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
	<WgpuBody url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
</Fragment>
